Sample Description: Comments on how to fill out each column of this form

Organism: Numbering of samples from 1 to the total number of samples. (This order is solely for convenient display, not used for sequencing.)
Informative sample identifier provided by submitter. Only use letters, numbers or underscores [A-Za-z0-9_], no other characters, please.
Summarizing description of the biological sample with biological context as required.
Full Latin name of the species and strain, or breeding scheme in case of hybrids.
Age and/or developmental stage of the organism, e.g. "81 years", "E14.5" or "Adult".
Tissue name or body part, e.g. "Liver", "Bone marrow" or "Cancer cell line".
Detailed description of cell type, e.g. "Lineage (CD4, CD8, CD3, B220, Ter119, Mac1, Gr1, Il7ra) negative, Sca1+, ckit+, CD34-, flk2-, PI-".
Any relevant genotype information, e.g. disease mutations or genetic modifications in transgenic mice.
Any available information on shared genotypes between samples, e.g. family trios or different samples from the same individual.
Any relevant phenotype information unrelated disease, e.g. "condensed cellular morphology" or "eye color: blue".
Disease status including comorbidities, e.g. "pT3N1, rectal adenocarcinoma; low grade" or "Undiagnosed autoimmune disease with severe systemic inflammation".
List of all biological material that is available for this sample, e.g. "Fresh-frozen cell pellets" or "DNA extracted from FFPE slices".
Person and/or lab providing the sample. If relevant, the full history of sample acquisition and sample processing should be provided.
Date when the sample was obtained by the submitter.

Additional columns should be added or removed as necessary in order to provide all relevant information pertaining to samples. Information associated with libraries should be entered into the separate "Libraries" table.
